1. background-color
background-color: color;
Color can be:
Named colors (red, blue, green, etc.)
HEX codes (#ff0000, #00ff00, etc.)
RGB values (rgb(255, 0, 0))
HSL values (hsl(0, 100%, 50%))

2. background-image

Syntax:
background-image: url('image.jpg');

Example:
background-image: url('background.png');

3. background-repeat
Definition: Controls how the background image is repeated.

Values:
repeat (default): The image repeats both horizontally and vertically.
repeat-x: Repeats only horizontally.
repeat-y: Repeats only vertically.
no-repeat: No repetition.

Example:
background-repeat: no-repeat;

4. background-position
Definition: Specifies the position of the background image.

Syntax:
background-position: x y;
Common values: left, right, top, bottom, center.
You can also use percentages or lengths (e.g., 50% 50% or 10px 20px).
Example:
background-position: center center;


5. background-size
Definition: Sets the size of the background image.
Values:
auto: Keeps the imageâ€™s original size.
cover: Scales the image to cover the entire element.
contain: Scales the image to fit inside the element.
Custom size: Specify width and height (100px 200px).
Example:
background-size: cover;


6. background-attachment
Definition: Controls whether the background image scrolls with the page or is fixed.
Values:
scroll (default): The background moves with the element.
fixed: The background stays fixed, even when scrolling.
local: The background scrolls with the content of the element.
Example:
background-attachment: fixed;

